80
00:04:15.700 --> 00:04:17.335
You've learned
throughout the course,

81
00:04:17.335 --> 00:04:20.855
test as you go, iterate,

82
00:04:20.855 --> 00:04:27.980
identify problems, use them
to improve the project.

83
00:04:27.980 --> 00:04:30.920
But ultimately you
reach the end.

84
00:04:30.920 --> 00:04:32.675
There's a point at which

85
00:04:32.675 --> 00:04:34.985
you can't carry on
developing more.

86
00:04:34.985 --> 00:04:37.520
In most projects, this isn't

87
00:04:37.520 --> 00:04:38.780
necessarily when you've done

88
00:04:38.780 --> 00:04:40.565
everything you've wanted to do.

89
00:04:40.565 --> 00:04:44.210
Most projects because
you're new to it,

90
00:04:44.210 --> 00:04:46.230
you've over-scoped it,

91
00:04:46.230 --> 00:04:48.500
you've said you do
more than you really

92
00:04:48.500 --> 00:04:51.110
can, to be honest,

93
00:04:51.110 --> 00:04:52.010
that happens quite a lot in

94
00:04:52.010 --> 00:04:53.590
professional projects as well,

95
00:04:53.590 --> 00:04:57.420
that's why agile methods
were developed really.

96
00:04:57.790 --> 00:05:02.430
They're developed to cope
with that over-scoping issue.

97
00:05:02.720 --> 00:05:06.255
But it does mean that there's
a certain point where

98
00:05:06.255 --> 00:05:10.095
you've decided it's enough,

99
00:05:10.095 --> 00:05:13.950
particularly given the time
constraints of your projects.

100
00:05:13.950 --> 00:05:17.880
You need to shift from how
to improve the project

101
00:05:17.880 --> 00:05:22.930
to assessing how well it
is succeeded overall.

102
00:05:24.650 --> 00:05:27.030
Has your project met

103
00:05:27.030 --> 00:05:29.880
the aims that you're
intending to achieve?

104
00:05:29.880 --> 00:05:31.665
That part is really important.

105
00:05:31.665 --> 00:05:34.600
You go back to the
beginning and think,

106
00:05:34.640 --> 00:05:38.340
the idea of this project
was based on the needs

107
00:05:38.340 --> 00:05:42.810
of this group of users or this
domain or this hypothesis.

108
00:05:42.810 --> 00:05:45.090
Have I answered the hypothesis?

109
00:05:45.090 --> 00:05:48.330
Have I addressed the
needs of the users?

110
00:05:48.330 --> 00:05:50.970
More importantly, how well?

111
00:05:50.970 --> 00:05:53.730
Hopefully most of you will
have done those things,

112
00:05:53.730 --> 00:05:58.620
but you might have done them
well in certain respects,

113
00:05:58.620 --> 00:06:00.840
and less well in other respects.

114
00:06:00.840 --> 00:06:04.050
You need to just balance those.

115
00:06:04.050 --> 00:06:05.430
How have I done that very well?

116
00:06:05.430 --> 00:06:07.680
How have I done it not so well?

117
00:06:07.680 --> 00:06:10.710
What is it doing this project

118
00:06:10.710 --> 00:06:13.110
told me about my
hypothesis and the users?

119
00:06:13.110 --> 00:06:14.250
You maybe have learned

120
00:06:14.250 --> 00:06:18.030
things that you weren't
aware of at the beginning,

121
00:06:18.030 --> 00:06:22.410
and maybe there's issues
with the hypothesis itself.

122
00:06:22.410 --> 00:06:25.380
Maybe it's just a little bit
more complicated than that.

123
00:06:25.380 --> 00:06:27.360
Maybe the needs of users
are just a bit more

124
00:06:27.360 --> 00:06:29.550
complicated than you
at first thought.

125
00:06:29.550 --> 00:06:32.370
Once you've actually put
software in front of people,

126
00:06:32.370 --> 00:06:35.580
you realize things that
you can't realize when

127
00:06:35.580 --> 00:06:41.550
you first researched them.

128
00:06:41.550 --> 00:06:48.510
They should be aware of
themselves when they start with.

129
00:06:48.510 --> 00:06:50.880
There's quite a lot of learning

130
00:06:50.880 --> 00:06:54.000
that you can do with
this evaluation stage.

131
00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:56.190
It's very important to do that.

132
00:06:56.190 --> 00:06:58.170
What does that final
evaluation look like?

133
00:06:58.170 --> 00:07:00.375
Well, it depends on
the kind of projects.

134
00:07:00.375 --> 00:07:02.130
You can have some
tests of you're

135
00:07:02.130 --> 00:07:04.050
hypothesis and data designs,

136
00:07:04.050 --> 00:07:07.410
you can do some
proper user testing,

137
00:07:07.410 --> 00:07:10.260
some final user testing

138
00:07:10.260 --> 00:07:14.265
or other forms of
software testing.

139
00:07:14.265 --> 00:07:16.200
But it's really about,

140
00:07:16.200 --> 00:07:20.100
it is a change of
focus from how do I

141
00:07:20.100 --> 00:07:24.960
improve this to what
have I achieved,

142
00:07:24.960 --> 00:07:27.250
how well have I achieved it?

143
00:07:27.440 --> 00:07:32.115
It's tempting to gloss over
problems at this stage.

144
00:07:32.115 --> 00:07:34.005
It's tempting to think,

145
00:07:34.005 --> 00:07:35.520
I'll present this
in the best light,

146
00:07:35.520 --> 00:07:36.390
so it's a good project.

147
00:07:36.390 --> 00:07:39.300
But don't do that.

148
00:07:39.300 --> 00:07:43.170
It's actually a very positive
activity or evaluation,

149
00:07:43.170 --> 00:07:47.025
if you're able to highlight
the bad as well as the good,

150
00:07:47.025 --> 00:07:50.865
or the issues, the things
that have changed.

151
00:07:50.865 --> 00:07:53.280
In many senses, as
a marker I'd always

152
00:07:53.280 --> 00:07:54.990
suspicious if somebody says,

153
00:07:54.990 --> 00:07:56.835
"Yes, I've achieved exactly
what I wanted to do."

154
00:07:56.835 --> 00:07:59.680
Nobody ever achieves exactly
what they want to do.

155
00:08:00.470 --> 00:08:05.309
Every single project
involves learning,

156
00:08:05.309 --> 00:08:06.750
and realizing things that

157
00:08:06.750 --> 00:08:09.250
are more complex
and more difficult.

158
00:08:09.650 --> 00:08:13.395
Bring those out and you'll
have a better evaluation.

159
00:08:13.395 --> 00:08:15.210
You assess very much
on the evaluation

160
00:08:15.210 --> 00:08:16.905
as well as the project itself.

161
00:08:16.905 --> 00:08:20.820
These are things are
all very important.

162
00:08:20.820 --> 00:08:22.260
How you do the evaluation will

163
00:08:22.260 --> 00:08:24.450
depend a lot on your project,

164
00:08:24.450 --> 00:08:27.405
a lot of suggestions
in your templates,

165
00:08:27.405 --> 00:08:29.460
but the general principle of

166
00:08:29.460 --> 00:08:32.670
how well have you
achieved the aims,

167
00:08:32.670 --> 00:08:35.655
what have you learned,
what's new is important.

168
00:08:35.655 --> 00:08:40.200
It can also include a certain
element of self-evaluation.

169
00:08:40.200 --> 00:08:41.490
How well have you done?

170
00:08:41.490 --> 00:08:43.125
What have you learned?

171
00:08:43.125 --> 00:08:45.540
What could you have done better

172
00:08:45.540 --> 00:08:50.610
or how has this changed your
thinking about projects?

173
00:08:50.610 --> 00:08:53.280
After all, this is a degree,

174
00:08:53.280 --> 00:08:58.065
this is really about
your learning.

175
00:08:58.065 --> 00:09:00.060
The write-up is primarily
about the project,

176
00:09:00.060 --> 00:09:01.500
but you can include a section if

177
00:09:01.500 --> 00:09:04.050
you want on self-evaluation,

178
00:09:04.050 --> 00:09:07.750
what have you learned.
That's good practice.

179
00:09:08.120 --> 00:09:12.610
Just to recap how we're
going to mark this.

